<HEADLINE> Sex counts get man lengthy sentence  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   SYRACUSE, N.Y. (AP) - Rejecting an offer to plead guilty to
reduced charges, a 43-year-old man was sentenced to serve between
25 to 50 years for the sodomy and rape of two young two girls.
</P>
<P>
   Gregory White's sentence was the maximum possible for the six
felony sex charges, and according to Madison County prosecutor
Renee Smith, he will have to serve at least 25 years before he
becomes eligible for parole.
</P>
<P>
   On Jan. 28, a Madison County jury found White guilty of
first-degree rape, second-degree rape, second-degree sodomy and
three counts of first-degree sodomy.
</P>
<P>
   White was convicted of raping a 13-year-old girl in 1995 and
forcing her and a 10-year-old girl to perform oral sex while they
played the children's game ''truth or dare.''
</P>
</TEXT>
