<HEADLINE> State Senate confirms Bellini as Monroe County judge  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   ALBANY, N.Y. (AP) - The state Senate confirmed the appointment
of Elma Bellini as a Monroe County Court judge.
</P>
<P>
   Bellini's term will begin immediately and run until Dec. 31. An
election for the seat will be held in November. Her salary will be
$125,600 a year.
</P>
<P>
   Bellini, 45, was recommended for the job by Gov. George Pataki.
Last year she ran for Monroe County district attorney. She has also
served as a partner at the Brent &AMP; Bellini law firm in Rochester.
</P>
<P>
   Bellini graduated from Syracuse University law school in 1986.
</P>
