<HEADLINE> Stocks Barely Changed Early On  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- The Dow Jones industrial average is up nine
points in today's early going. Losing issues on the New York Stock
Exchange hold an 11-10 lead over gainers.
</P>
<P>
   The Nasdaq Composite Index is off two points and the Standard &AMP;
Poor's 500 Stock Index is virtually unchanged.
</P>
<P>
   Analysts say today's economic numbers likely will have little
impact on Wall Street, since yesterday's retail inflation numbers
received no big reaction.
</P>
<P>
   The government released numbers today on industrial production
and new claims for jobless benefits.
</P>
<P>
   There could be some choppy action again today, however, since
the market does tend to be somewhat volatile ahead of a
triple-witching session.
</P>
<P>
   Wall Street will have one of those session tomorrow, featuring
the simultaneous expirations of stock index futures, stock index
options and the options on individual stocks.
</P>
