<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Perry Withdraws From Emmy Contest  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES (AP) -- Matthew Perry proved himself a real pal,
asking that his name be withdrawn from Emmy consideration because
he was entered in the best actor category by mistake.
</P>
<P>
   Since the debut of ''Friends'' on NBC, the ensemble cast has
presented a united front, each seeking only supporting actor
nominations. Perry's publicist, Lisa Kasteler, said her office
erred this year by touting him as a leading actor nominee.
</P>
<P>
   Perry immediately asked that the Academy of Television Arts &AMP;
Sciences withdraw his name. Emmy ballots went out June 5, so it's
too late for him to be named in another category.
</P>
<P>
   ''There are things more important to Matthew than awards,''
Kasteler said. ''He didn't want to separate himself from his
co-stars.''
</P>
<P>
   Perry's withdrawal means only David Schwimmer and Lisa Kudrow
have been nominated for Emmys from the ''Friends'' cast. Schwimmer
was nominated during the show's first season, 1994-95. Kudrow,
nominated twice, won best supporting actress in a sitcom in 1998.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER> AP-NY-06-15-00 1351 </TRAILER>
</DOC>
