<HEADLINE> Candice Bergen May Tie Knot Again  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA (AP) -- Candice Bergen says she feels too old to be
engaged, but that won't prevent her from tying the knot with New
York businessman and philanthropist Marshall Rose.
</P>
<P>
   ''What's the point, really?'' Bergen, 54, said Tuesday night
after giving a lecture at the Atlanta Civic Center. ''But, yes, we
may formalize it. You heard it here first.''
</P>
<P>
   She gave no wedding date. Bergen's former husband, French
director Louis Malle, died of cancer in 1995.
</P>
<P>
   Bergen, perhaps best known for her 10-year CBS role as
television reporter ''Murphy Brown,'' said she agreed to be host of
an interview show on the cable channel Oxygen as a way to reinvent
herself. But she said the Brown character is hard to escape.
</P>
<P>
   ''I always kind of feel like she's sitting on my shoulder,
yelling in my ear, 'You moron, don't do that!'''
</P>
