<HEADLINE> Weaver, Hewitt To Play Con Artists  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   PALM BEACH, Fla. (AP) -- Sigourney Weaver and Jennifer Love
Hewitt will star as a mother-daughter con artist team in a movie
named after a trendy Palm Beach resort.
</P>
<P>
   ''The Breakers,'' in which Weaver and Hewitt fleece wealthy,
lonely men out of their fortunes at the five-star, seaside hotel,
is set to begin filming in mid-July.
</P>
<P>
   The women take aim on Gene Hackman, who plays the richest man in
Palm Beach. Also starring in the $25 million film are Anne
Bancroft, Ray Liotta and Jason Lee.
</P>
<P>
   Though producers say most of the movie will be shot on a
Hollywood set, the hotel will serve as a backdrop, and a few shots
will be filmed on the island town's shopping street, Worth Avenue.
</P>
