<HEADLINE> Court Rejects Alec Baldwin's Appeal  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   SAN FRANCISCO (AP) -- Alec Baldwin can now get on with his life.
</P>
<P>
   The California Supreme Court said Wednesday it won't review a
lower court ruling that a celebrity photographer is not entitled to
recover the costs of a lawsuit he filed against the actor.
</P>
<P>
   The legal wrangling stems from a 1995 fight that broke out after
Alan Zanger videotaped Baldwin and his wife, actress Kim Basinger,
with their newborn daughter, Ireland.
</P>
<P>
   Baldwin sprayed Zanger's truck with shaving cream and broke his
nose and his glasses. Baldwin claimed he was defending himself.
</P>
<P>
   Baldwin was acquitted of misdemeanor battery in a 1996 trial,
but found partly to blame for the fight in a separate proceeding.
Zanger's appeal asked for $18,000 in legal costs.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
