<HEADLINE> Big Movers in the Stock Market  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Stocks that were moving substantially or trading
heavily Thursday on the New York Stock Exchange and Nasdaq Stock
Market.
</P>
<P>
NYSE
Lucent Technologies Inc., up $3.063 at $59.688
</P>
<P>
   The telecommunications-equipment maker is considering plans to
spin off its microelectronics unit in a deal analysts say could be
valued at more than $50 billion, according to published reports. In
addition, Lucent agreed to become the primary communications
infrastructure supplier for Verizon Wireless, providing up to $1.5
billion worth of products to the nation's largest wireless
provider.
</P>
<P>
Wachovia Corp., down $13.125 at $57.063
</P>
<P>
   The Winston-Salem, N.C.-based company said its second-quarter
and full-year earnings and revenue would fall below analyst
estimates. The financial holding company said the shortfall is due
to rising interest rates, which tempered growth in its capital
markets, mortgage and investment businesses, and caused reduced
margins in lending.
</P>
<P>
International Flavors &AMP; Fragrances Inc., down $2.25 at $32
</P>
<P>
   The maker of aromas and flavors expects to earn about 48 cents a
share for the second quarter, flat with last year's earnings before
charges, and below Wall Street analysts' estimates of 53 cents a
share.
</P>
<P>
