</P>
<P>
   Salomon Smith Barney upgraded the soft-drink maker's shares
because efforts to localize its business are beginning to pay off.
In addition, the company said it reached a tentative deal to settle
a race discrimination lawsuit from current and former employees.
However, that settlement came just as the company was saddled with
a separate racial discrimination suit.
</P>
<P>
