<HEADLINE> Teacher accused of having sex with 14-year-old student  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   HACKENSACK, N.J. (AP) - An eighth-grade teacher was arrested and
accused of having sex with a 14-year-old female student of his, the
Bergen County Prosecutor's Office said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
   Jeffrey Levine had sex on ''numerous'' occasions with the girl
since April at his home in East Rutherford and at the Hackensack
Middle School, where he taught, Assistant Bergen County Prosecutor
Patricia Baglivi said.
</P>
<P>
   She said authorities were alerted to the relationship by a
''third party,'' but declined to be more specific.
</P>
<P>
   Levine, 27, came to the Prosecutor's Office Wednesday night to
answer questions and was arrested sometime late that night or early
Thursday, Baglivi said.
</P>
<P>
   He was immediately suspended from teaching, pending the outcome
of the investigation, said Joseph L. Montesano, the Hackensack
school superintendent. The Board of Education is likely to halt
Levine's salary, he said.
</P>
<P>
   Levine, completing his first year as a full-time teacher, had
been a substitute teacher for a year or two, Montesano said. Levine
taught remedial English.
</P>
<P>
   Levine was held Thursday on $300,000 bail, no 10 percent option,
set by state Superior Court Judge Sebastian Gaeta Jr., Baglivi
said.
</P>
<P>
   He is charged with one count of aggravated sexual assault and
two counts of endangering the welfare of a child.
</P>
