<HEADLINE> Vermont bank robber may have headed to New York  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   NORTH BENNINGTON, Vt. (AP) - An armed man robbed a bank early
Wednesday and fled, possibly toward New York.
</P>
<P>
   The robbery at Merchants Bank took place at 1 p.m. Vermont State
Police and Bennington officers were looking for a white male about
5 feet 10 inches, who was wearing light blue clothing, wire glasses
and a homemade mask.
</P>
<P>
   During the holdup the suspect displayed a gun, later described
as a semiautomatic weapon, police said.
</P>
<P>
   Using a hat found at the scene and believed worn by the bandit,
a police dog tracked the trail to a railroad bed that heads west
toward New York.
</P>
<P>
   Bennington Police Department officials did not release
information on how much money, if any, was taken.
</P>
<P>
   There had been no arrest as of 10 p.m. Thursday.
</P>
<P>
   Bennington is 34 miles northeast of Albany.
</P>
</TEXT>
