<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Lynx 72, Miracle 66  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   MINNEAPOLIS (AP) -- Betty Lennox scored a career-high 25 points
and Katie Smith had 24 as the Minnesota Lynx beat the Orlando
Miracle 72-66 on Thursday night to extend their winning streak to a
franchise-record four games.
</P>
<P>
   Sonja Tate added 13 points for Minnesota, which scored 23 points
off 24 Orlando turnovers. Smith shot 12-for-12 from the foul line
to set a franchise record.
</P>
<P>
   Nykesha Sales scored 23 points, including a four-point play, and
Adrienne Johnson added 20 for the Miracle. Cintia dos Santos had a
career-high 11 rebounds for Orlando, which had won two straight.
</P>
<P>
   Minnesota shot just 34.9 from the field to Orlando's 46.3.
</P>
<P>
   After the teams traded baskets for the first six minutes of the
second half, the Lynx outscored the Miracle 17-9 to take a 56-46
lead with 6:42 left. Orlando did not get closer than four points
the rest of the way.
</P>
<P>
   Orlando shot 52.2 percent in the first half and Minnesota shot
just 29.7 percent, but the Lynx led 32-31 at the break. The
difference was that Minnesota shot 8-for-8 at the foul line and
forced 16 Miracle turnovers.
</P>
<P>
   Lennox also had six rebounds.
</P>
<P>
   The Lynx had a three-game winning streak last season.
</P>
</TEXT>
