<HEADLINE> Monaco Pricess' Husband Collapses  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   CELLE, Germany (AP) -- Princess Caroline of Monaco's husband
collapsed Thursday at a reception in this northern German town and
was taken to a hospital, police said.
</P>
<P>
   What ailment caused Prince Ernst August of Hanover, 46, to
collapse was not immediately clear, Celle police said. He was first
brought to the local hospital, then transported by helicopter to
the nearby city of Hanover, the police said.
</P>
<P>
   Ernst August had accompanied Caroline, her brother Albert and
their father, Prince Rainier of Monaco, earlier Thursday during a
visit to the World's Fair in Hanover. In the evening, Rainier had
hosted the reception at a castle in Celle.
</P>
<P>
   Ernst August is descended from one of Germany's oldest noble
families. He and Caroline wed in January 1999, the third marriage
for her and the second for him. They have an 11-month-old daughter,
Alexandra.
</P>
