<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-15 22:22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> BC-NY--Mayor-Harassment, 3rd Ld-Writethru, 640  </HEADLINE>
AP Photos
<TEXT>
<P>
   UTICA, N.Y. (AP) - Four men have accused Utica Mayor Ed Hanna of
sexual harassment.
</P>
<P>
   The men, two former and two current city employees, claim the
78-year-old mayor made unwelcome sexual advances as a term of their
employment.
</P>
<P>
   ''The basis of the claims are allegations of sexual harassment
at the work place that was a condition of employment,'' Frank
Policelli, the attorney representing the four men, said Thursday.
''He (Hanna) made unwelcome advances toward all of the men and had
contact with at least one of them.''
</P>
<P>
   Policelli filed a notice of claim on Wednesday as a prelude to a
federal lawsuit. When the lawsuit is filed in 30 days, a dollar
amount will be stated, he said.
</P>
<P>
   The plaintiffs are: Joseph Pouliot, 23, of Holland Patent;
Joseph DiPierro, 22, of Utica; Nathan Newman, 24, of Utica; and
Patrick Van Etten, 35, also of Utica. Pouliot and Newman are still
employed by the city, while three of the four at one time held the
title of assistant to the mayor, Policelli said.
</P>
<P>
   ''They were all there (working in the mayor's office) at
different times,'' Policelli said. ''But their testimony will be
substantially the same as far as a pattern of conduct. The office
was used merely as a way of satisfying his sexual desires.''
</P>
<P>
   Policelli said one incident allegedly happened May 16, after one
of the plaintiffs had been on the job for only a week.
</P>
<P>
   ''He was able to record a conversation with the mayor (after the
incident), which helped substantiate his claim,'' Policelli said,
adding that he also had a second tape to use for evidence. ''I
think we've got a pretty strong case.''
</P>
<P>
   Hanna denied the allegations.
</P>
<P>
   ''It's a scam, loaded with outrageous lies,'' Hanna said in a
statement faxed to local news organizations Wednesday. ''Everything
stated that is damaging and ugly is a fabricated and out-of-context
manipulation, in a cleverly orchestrated conspiracy to extort
money, including political rewards and control.''
</P>
<P>
   Policelli said that during the course of his monthlong
investigation of the alleged incident in May, the other men came
forward on their own.
</P>
<P>
   Policelli said Van Etten was installing a phone one day when the
mayor saw him and decided to make him an assistant mayor. According
to Policelli, when Van Etten refused the mayor's advances he was
assigned to another department and then fired after seven weeks on
the job.
</P>
<P>
   Newman said in a deposition that Hanna invited him to his home
on several occasions, asked him questions about his sexual
practices, and invited him to watch a pornographic movie.
</P>
<P>
   The mayor was re-elected to his fourth - and final - four-year
term in November. Term limits set the maximum number of times a
person can hold the office.
</P>
<P>
   Hanna, who also served in the state Legislature in the 1950s and
again in 1966 after winning election to a special one-year term,
has been no stranger to controversy in his long and colorful
political career.
</P>
<P>
   After he was first elected Utica mayor in 1973, he removed his
office door to so he would be more accessible to the people. He
later had it reinstalled.
</P>
<P>
   Hanna, who once served as state Parks Commissioner, also tried
to fire the entire Public Works Department during a labor dispute,
and at one point was arrested by a police chief he tried to fire
after he broke into the chief's office.
</P>
<P>
   Hanna also announced plans to run for the U.S. Senate in 1976,
mayor of Utica in 1979, and state Assembly in 1980 before
withdrawing from each race.
</P>
<P>
   A high school dropout and World War II combat Marine, Hanna made
a fortune in the photochemical industry before entering politics.
His erratic style has made him the subject of several national
magazine and newspaper articles.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
