<HEADLINE> Comatose lawyer subject of child porn investigation  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   HAMPTON, Va. (AP) - A local lawyer who was left comatose by a
New Jersey highway crash is under investigation for child
pornography based on a police search of his vehicle after the
accident, court records indicate.
</P>
<P>
   Kenneth A. Eusner, who was semiretired from his Hampton law
practice, was changing a flat tire on the Garden State Parkway on
June 4 when he was struck by a car. He suffered severe leg
injuries, police said.
</P>
<P>
   After being taken to Hackensack University Medical Center,
Eusner suffered a heart attack and lapsed into a coma. A hospital
spokesman said Thursday that he was in critical condition.
</P>
<P>
   In a search warrant affidavit filed by New Jersey State Police
with the Hampton Circuit Court, investigators said they found
''numerous pornographic photographs, including 49 obvious
pornographic photographs of children under the age of 16'' in
Eusner's vehicle.
</P>
<P>
   Also found in the vehicle was a substance suspected to be
heroin, a .45-caliber handgun and ammunition, a .22-caliber rifle,
a .12-gauge shotgun and two knives, the document said.
</P>
<P>
   A special agent from the Virginia State Police Bureau of
Criminal Investigation searched Eusner's home this week and seized
a computer with the serial number obliterated, as well as floppy
disks, videotapes, photographs and e-mail, according to the
document.
</P>
<P>
   Bob Jasinowski, head of state police investigations for the
Chesapeake division, declined to comment on the investigation.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
