Blues' Pronger MVP, Top Defenseman
</SUBHEAD>
<P>
   TORONTO (AP) -- Chris Pronger was a triple winner tonight, taking home NHL
awards as the most valuable player and top defenseman and making the All-Star
team. The 25-year-old St. Louis Blues star is the first defenseman since Bobby
Orr in 1972 to win the Hart Memorial Trophy. He got the MVP honors in the
closest balloting in the award's history, beating out scoring champion Jaromir
Jagr and top goal scorer Pavel Bure.
</P>
