<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Comets 77, Sol 53  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   HOUSTON (AP) -- Tina Thompson scored 20 points and Cynthia Cooper
had 18 as the three-time defending WNBA champion Houston Comets
routed the expansion Miami Sol 77-53 on Thursday night.
</P>
<P>
   Sheryl Swoopes added 16 points for the Comets, who led 44-13 at
the half and 53-15 early in the second half. Houston has won four
straight to improve to 8-1.
</P>
<P>
   Thompson, Cooper and Swoopes combined for 42 of Houston's 44
first-half points. Thompson had 17 points in the half, Cooper 13
and Swoopes 12.
</P>
<P>
   Katrina Colleton led Miami with 10 points.
</P>
<P>
   The Sol (2-5) were 18-for-52 from the field, including a
3-for-11 mark from 3-point range. Miami dropped to 2-5.
</P>
</TEXT>
