<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-15 23:43 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hill, Paisley Win at TNN Awards  </HEADLINE>
By JIM PATTERSON
<TEXT>
<P>
   NASHVILLE, Tenn. (AP) -- An absent George Strait swept five
categories at the TNN Awards for country music Thursday, with
newcomer Brad Paisley nipping at his heels with his popular song
celebrating stepparents.
</P>
<P>
   Strait won the top award of best entertainer, best male
vocalist, best album for ''Always Never The Same'' and single for
''Write This Down.''
</P>
<P>
   He also got the Impact Award, given for getting country music
exposure in advertisements, television and movies. Strait is a
commercial spokesman for Wrangler jeans and other products.
</P>
<P>
   ''Thanks to all the fans,'' said MCA Records executive Tony
Brown, who produces Strait's records. ''George is the greatest.
He's the king of the cowboys!''
</P>
<P>
   Paisley won the newly created Discovery Award, given to a new
artist with the most star potential. His ''He Didn't Have to Be''
won for best song and video.
</P>
<P>
   The song was written by Paisley and Kelley Lovelace about
Lovelace's relationship with his stepson. Paisley brought Lovelace
and the 9-year-old boy, McCain Merren, onstage to share the glory
when he won best song.
</P>
<P>
   ''The greatest thing about country music is you can write a song
that you think is so personal that there's no way it could be
anybody else's story,'' Paisley said. ''And you find out that we
are all the same.''
</P>
<P>
   Faith Hill won best female vocalist, and the Dixie Chicks were
named best group or duo.
</P>
<P>
   The quartet Alabama tearfully accepted an award for charity work
named after the late comedian Minnie Pearl. Kenny Rogers, who
recently scored comeback hits with ''The Greatest'' and ''Buy Me a
Rose,'' won a career achievement award.
</P>
<P>
   ''For the last 10-12 years ... I've been giving out these
awards, and doing it with as much grace as I possibly could,''
Rogers said. ''But it's a wonderful thing to receive an award, and
particularly at this point in my life.''
</P>
<P>
   Eleven-year-old singer Billy Gilman introduced a medley of
performances by veteran artists Loretta Lynn, Ronnie Milsap and The
Charlie Daniels Band.
</P>
<P>
   The TNN Awards cap International Country Music Fan Fair, an
annual week of performances and autograph sessions that draw more
than 20,000 fans to Nashville.
</P>
<P>
   This year marked a new sponsor for the TNN Awards. Country
Weekly magazine has replaced Music City News, which recently
folded.
</P>
<P>
   The nominations came from fans and music industry workers. Fans
voted for the winners through telephone numbers announced on TNN,
ballots in Country Weekly magazine and two Internet sites.
</P>
<P>
   The TNN Awards are the second of three major annual country
music awards shows, and the only one that gives fans a voice in
choosing winners. The others are the Country Music Association
awards in the fall and the Academy of Country Music awards in the
spring.
------
</P>
<P>
   On the Net:
</P>
<P>
   TNN: http://www.country.com
</P>
<P>
   Country Weekly magazine: http://www.countryweekly.com.
</P>
</TEXT>
